 not work if there is no power at the receiver.";i:37;s:118:"Check for Blocked Safety Sensors The safety sensors are located near the bottom rear corners of the garage door track.";i:38;s:43:"Take the remote opener and test the ranges.";i:39;s:95:"If the range improves you can unplug everything inside of the garage and switch on the breaker.";i:40;s:84:"Plug the opener back in inside of the garage and test the other items one at a time.";i:41;s:72:"If you find the item causing interference simply move it somewhere else.";i:42;s:32:"Garage Door Opener Losing Range.";i:43;s:94:"There are many reasons that your remote control will only work when it is close to the opener.";i:44;s:51:"Below is a list of some issues that may cause this.";i:45;s:43:"Issues with the wires to the control panel.";}}